                        Santorini Dream Tour Package:
                    </button>
                  </h2>
                  <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Day 1: Arrival in Santorini

                        Arrive at Santorini Airport or Port.
                        Transfer to your hotel in Santorini.
                        Check-in and relax after your journey.
                        Enjoy a leisurely evening exploring the local area.
                        Day 2: Island Exploration
                        
                        Morning: Guided tour of Fira, the capital of Santorini. Explore the charming streets, visit local shops, and take in panoramic views of the caldera.
                        Afternoon: Visit Oia, famous for its stunning sunsets and picturesque blue-domed churches. Explore the village, visit art galleries, and enjoy local cuisine at a waterfront restaurant.
                        Evening: Watch the sunset from one of the best viewpoints in Oia.
                        Day 3: Volcano and Hot Springs Excursion
                        
                        Morning: Take a boat tour to the volcanic islands of Nea Kameni and Palea Kameni. Hike to the crater of the volcano and learn about Santorini's volcanic history.
                        Afternoon: Visit the nearby hot springs for a relaxing swim in the therapeutic waters.
                        Evening: Return to Santorini and enjoy a traditional Greek dinner at a local taverna.
                        Day 4: Beach Day
                        
                        Morning: Relax and unwind at one of Santorini's beautiful beaches. Options include Kamari Beach, Perissa Beach, or Red Beach.
                        Afternoon: Optional water sports activities such as snorkeling, scuba diving, or jet skiing.
                        Evening: Enjoy a sunset cruise around the caldera, with dinner and drinks onboard.
                        Day 5: Wine Tasting Tour
                        
                        Morning: Explore the vineyards of Santorini on a guided wine tasting tour. Visit local wineries, sample unique varietals such as Assyrtiko, and learn about the island's winemaking traditions.
                        Afternoon: Visit the traditional village of Pyrgos and explore its historic castle and winding alleys.
                        Evening: Farewell dinner at a rooftop restaurant with panoramic views of the island.
                        Day 6: Departure
                        <br>
                        <a href="https://www.santosails.com/sailing-cruises/full-day-sailing-cruise/?gad_source=1&gclid=Cj0KCQjw-_mvBhDwARIsAA-Q0Q5NrBmMKxrHNJra_4o0xyoY12CQxaLzUV5Y88aSjN2EXl99aD4w_1waAgWqEALw_wcB" class="btn btn-primary">View details</a>

                  <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Day 1: Arrival in Kyoto

                        Arrive at Kansai International Airport or Osaka Itami Airport.
                        Transfer to your hotel in Kyoto.
                        Check-in and relax after your journey.
                        Evening at leisure to explore the local area and enjoy dinner at a traditional Japanese restaurant.
                        Day 2: Cultural Exploration
                        
                        Morning: Guided tour of Kinkaku-ji (Golden Pavilion), one of Kyoto's most iconic landmarks.
                        Afternoon: Visit Ryoan-ji Temple, known for its famous rock garden, and explore the nearby Arashiyama district, famous for its bamboo groves and Togetsukyo Bridge.
                        Evening: Attend a traditional tea ceremony and learn about the art of Japanese tea.
                        Day 3: Historic Sites and Shrines
                        
                        Morning: Explore Fushimi Inari Taisha, the famous Shinto shrine known for its thousands of vermillion torii gates.
                        Afternoon: Visit Kiyomizu-dera Temple, a UNESCO World Heritage Site with panoramic views of Kyoto city.
                        Evening: Stroll through the historic Gion district, known for its traditional machiya houses and geisha culture. Optional dinner at a local izakaya (Japanese pub).
                        Day 4: Day Trip to Nara
                        
                        Full-day excursion to Nara, Japan's ancient capital and home to some of the country's oldest and most significant temples and shrines.
                        Visit Todai-ji Temple, home to the Great Buddha statue, and Nara Park, where you can interact with friendly wild deer.
                        Return to Kyoto in the evening and enjoy dinner at a local restaurant.
                        Day 5: Kyoto Imperial Palace and Gardens
                        
                        Morning: Guided tour of Kyoto Imperial Palace, the former residence of Japan's imperial family.
                        Afternoon: Explore the beautiful gardens of Kyoto, including the Kyoto Botanical Garden and the Kyoto Imperial Palace East Garden.
                        Evening: Farewell dinner at a traditional kaiseki restaurant, enjoying a multi-course meal featuring seasonal ingredients.
                        Day 6: Departure

                        Machu Picchu Adventure Tour Package:
                    </button>

                  <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Day 1: Arrival in Cusco

                        Arrive at Alejandro Velasco Astete International Airport in Cusco.
                        Transfer to your hotel in Cusco's historic center, a UNESCO World Heritage Site.
                        Check-in and acclimatize to the altitude (3,399 meters above sea level).
                        Optional guided walking tour of Cusco's main attractions, including Plaza de Armas, Cathedral of Santo Domingo, and Qorikancha (Temple of the Sun).
                        Evening at leisure to explore the vibrant nightlife and local cuisine.
                        Day 2: Sacred Valley Excursion
                        
                        Full-day guided tour of the Sacred Valley of the Incas.
                        Visit Pisac Market, where you can shop for traditional handicrafts and souvenirs.
                        Explore the archaeological site of Ollantaytambo, an ancient Inca fortress with terraces and temples.
                        Lunch at a local restaurant featuring Andean cuisine.
                        Return to Cusco in the evening.
                        Day 3: Train to Aguas Calientes
                        
                        Morning: Transfer to Ollantaytambo Train Station.
                        Board the scenic train to Aguas Calientes, the gateway to Machu Picchu.
                        Arrive in Aguas Calientes and check into your hotel.
                        Afternoon at leisure to explore the town and visit the hot springs for relaxation.
                        Optional visit to the Manuel Chávez Ballón Museum to learn about Machu Picchu's history and discovery.
                        Day 4: Machu Picchu Exploration
                        
                        Early morning: Take the bus from Aguas Calientes to Machu Picchu, one of the New Seven Wonders of the World.
                        Guided tour of Machu Picchu, exploring its terraces, temples, and residential areas while learning about its history and significance.
                        Optional hike to Huayna Picchu or Machu Picchu Mountain for panoramic views of the citadel and surrounding mountains.
                        Return to Aguas Calientes in the afternoon.
                        Day 5: Return to Cusco
                        
                        Morning: Optional return visit to Machu Picchu for sunrise or further exploration on your own.
                        Board the train back to Ollantaytambo.
                        Transfer to Cusco and check into your hotel.
                        Evening at leisure for shopping, dining, and cultural activities in Cusco.
                        Day 6: Departure
